{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_015M7qgF5TUzpb7o8Trw5xrF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019DjbeuFYNxDhF8Yp9DwT5G","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Conversation history trimmed to most recent 10 messages when context window is exceeded","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The trimming logic is pure list manipulation with no I/O or LLM dependency. Real failures (off-by-one errors, trimming wrong slice, boundary conditions on < 10 messages) can be caught by directly testing the trimming function with realistic message data structures. No mock can hide a slicing bug.","test_description":"Create test message histories of varying sizes (5, 10, 15, 20+ messages). Call the trim function and verify: output is exactly the last 10 messages, ordering is preserved, messages before index -10 are excluded. Test boundary: history with < 10 messages should remain unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Generated response addresses the customer's question rather than producing generic or off-topic reply","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is a correctness property that depends entirely on what the real LLM produces. Mocking the LLM to return 'on-topic' responses always passes the test, masking real failures where the prompt is poorly designed or ambiguous. A real LLM may produce off-topic or generic responses depending on temperature, model state, and prompt clarity. The failure boundary is the actual LLM behavior, not code logic.","test_description":"Call the real LLM with diverse customer questions (across multiple tiers: premium, standard, casual). Collect responses and evaluate on-topicness using either: (a) heuristics (response contains keywords from the question), (b) another LLM as judge, or (c) manual spot-check. Test that across multiple runs, the vast majority of responses directly address the customer's stated problem rather than generic placeholders.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Tone re-check correctly identifies when response is too formal for casual-tier customer and triggers regeneration","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The tone checker likely depends on an LLM or ML classification model. Its correctness varies with real model output. Mocking the tone checker (always returning 'pass' or 'fail') hides the real failure: the model's accuracy at detecting formality. The failure boundary is whether the tone model actually learns to distinguish formal from casual language. Real outputs vary; a mocked return never does.","test_description":"Feed the tone checker with real response examples: (1) intentionally formal responses (e.g., 'I acknowledge receipt of your inquiry...') and (2) intentionally casual responses (e.g., 'Hey! Happy to help with that'). For a casual-tier customer, verify the formal responses are flagged as 'too_formal' and trigger regeneration, while casual ones pass. Test across multiple response styles to ensure the model catches the pattern, not just one example.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Full exchange (user message, generated response, regenerations) persisted to database with correct timestamps","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Persistence to a real database is the critical failure boundary. Mocking the database layer means all writes 'succeed' in the mock, hiding real failures: schema mismatches, timestamp serialization bugs, partial writes on transaction failure, or incorrect timezone handling. The real failure occurs in the database layer, not in code logic. Integration test with a real (or containerized test) database is required.","test_description":"Using a real test database (SQLite or PostgreSQL): (1) Call the service with a user message and history, (2) Force a tone-check regeneration so the exchange includes the first response, regeneration flag, and final response, (3) Query the database directly to verify: all messages are present, timestamps are in correct format and timezone, the full exchange chain is recorded, and no partial writes occurred. Verify data integrity after a simulated failure (transaction rollback).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — customer never sees rejected draft","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This tests control flow and response selection logic within a service. The failure is a code bug: returning or showing the first response after regeneration, or both responses. A unit test mocking the LLM (to return different responses on first and second call) and the tone checker (to trigger regeneration) can verify the service selects and returns the regenerated response. No I/O, no real LLM correctness issue—just orchestration logic.","test_description":"Mock LLM to return two different responses in sequence (e.g., 'formal_response' then 'casual_response'). Mock tone_checker to flag the first as 'too_formal'. Call the service's response handler. Verify: (1) the returned response to the customer is 'casual_response', not 'formal_response', (2) LLM was called twice (first and regeneration), (3) tone_checker was called and its result was acted upon. Test with various response values to ensure the logic always picks the final regenerated response.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13312,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13312},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bfdd4d28-65b0-473e-9dd4-e6b5db760799","uuid":"dec5d2f9-ab12-4cc6-9d1d-50a8d82e8cbf"}
